Class WelshMorph

  • java.lang.Object
    • gate.util.AbstractFeatureBearer
      • gate.creole.AbstractResource
        • gate.creole.AbstractProcessingResource
          • gate.creole.AbstractLanguageAnalyser
            • wnlt.morph.WelshMorph
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    gate.creole.ANNIEConstants, gate.creole.CustomDuplication, gate.Executable, gate.LanguageAnalyser, gate.ProcessingResource, gate.Resource, gate.util.Benchmarkable, gate.util.FeatureBearer, gate.util.NameBearer, java.io.Serializable

    @CreoleResource(name="GATE Morphological analyser",
                comment="Morphological Analyzer of the Welsh Natural Language Toolkit")
public class WelshMorph
extends gate.creole.AbstractLanguageAnalyser
implements gate.ProcessingResource, gate.creole.CustomDuplication, gate.util.Benchmarkable
    Description: This class is a wrapper for Interpret, the Morphological Analyzer. The class is based on and modifies for the purposes of the Welsh Natural Language Toolkit the Morph class of the GATE Morphological analyser.
    Author:
    Andreas Vlachidis 20/03/2016
    See Also:

        public gate.Resource init()

        This method creates the instance of the BaseWord - Welsh Morpher and returns the instance of current class with different attributes and the instance of BaseWord class wrapped into it. The method also instantiates the post-processing transducer, and mutation validation gazetteer and transducer

      • cleanup

        public void cleanup()
        Method is executed after the init() method has finished its execution.
        Method does the following operations:
        1. creates the annotationSet
        2. fetches word tokens from the document, one at a time
        3. runs the morpher on each individual word token
        4. finds the root and the affix for that word
        5. adds them as features to the current token
        Specified by:
        cleanup in interface gate.Resource
        Overrides:
        cleanup in class gate.creole.AbstractProcessingResource
        Throws:
        gate.creole.ExecutionException
